Such an approach would lead to inconsistency and confusion for users, undermining the practicality of using a minimal GNOME setup.

No comparable issues exist for LXQt. Users have the advantage of leveraging both Debian and LXQt documentation, along with resources from third parties, to customize and utilize LXQt effectively.

