= Usability =

'''Systray Absence:''' By default, GNOME does not include a systray.

How can it be added?

* For typical GNOME users, the recommended method is to visit: [https://extensions.gnome.org/extension/615/appindicator-support/ AppIndicator Support] and click the 'Install' button.
* Command line: For users who want to install from the command line, via packages.debian.org or from source code, while performing digital software signature verification: Unknown.
* Linux distributions: For distributions using a build script, the process remains unclear. ([[Dev/Derivative-Maker#Introduction|Clicking buttons is inappropriate for Linux distribution build scripts.]]) If a solution for the command line becomes available, it might also provide insight into this scenario.

